      • mostEnergyEfficientRouteBetweenTwoParks

        long mostEnergyEfficientRouteBetweenTwoParks(String originParkIdentification,
                                             String destinationParkIdentification,
                                             String typeOfVehicle,
                                             String vehicleSpecs,
                                             String username,
                                             String outputFileName)
        Calculate the most energy efficient route from one park to another. Basic: Does not consider wind. Intermediate: Considers wind. Advanced: Considers the different mechanical and aerodynamic coefficients.
        Parameters:
        originParkIdentification - Origin Park Identification.
        destinationParkIdentification - Destination Park Identification.
        typeOfVehicle - The type of vehicle required e.g. "bicycle" or "escooter".
        vehicleSpecs - The specs for the vehicle e.g. "16", "19", "27" or any other number for bicyles and "city" or "off-road" for any escooter.
        username - The username.
        outputFileName - Write to the file the Route between two parks according to file output/paths.csv. More than one path may exist. If so, sort routes by the ascending number of points between the parks and by ascending order of elevation difference.
        Returns:
        The distance in meters for the most energy efficient path.

      • getUserCurrentDebt

                          String outputFileName)
        Return the current debt for the user.
        Parameters:

        outputFileName - The path for the file to output the debt, according to file output/balance.csv. Sort the information by unlock time in ascending order (oldest to newest).
        Returns:
        The User's current debt in euros, rounded to two decimal places.

      • shortestRouteBetweenTwoParks

        long shortestRouteBetweenTwoParks(double originLatitudeInDegrees,
                                  double originLongitudeInDegrees,
                                  double destinationLatitudeInDegrees,
                                  double destinationLongitudeInDegrees,
                                  int numberOfPOIs,
                                  String outputFileName)
        Calculate the shortest Route from one park to another. Basic: Only one shortest Route between two Parks is available. Advanced: More than one Route between two parks are available with different number of POIs (limit to a maximum of two) inbetween and different evelations difference.
        Parameters:
        originLatitudeInDegrees - Origin latitude in Decimal degrees.
        originLongitudeInDegrees - Origin Longitude in Decimal degrees.
        destinationLatitudeInDegrees - Destination Park latitude in Decimal degrees.
        destinationLongitudeInDegrees - Destination Park Longitude in Decimal degrees.
        numberOfPOIs - The number of POIs that should be included in the path. Default can be 0.
        outputFileName - Write to the file the Route between two parks according to file output/paths.csv. More than one path may exist. If so, sort routes by the ascending number of points between the parks and by ascending order of elevation difference.
        Returns:
        The distance in meters for the shortest path.

      • shortestRouteBetweenTwoParks

        destinationParkIdentification - Destination Park Identification.

      • getParkChargingReport

        originParkIdentification - Origin Park Identification.
        destinationParkIdentification - Destination Park Identification.
        typeOfVehicle - The type of vehicle required e.g. "bicycle" or "escooter".
        vehicleSpecs - The specs for the vehicle e.g. "16", "19", "27" or any other number for bicyles and "city" or "off-road" for any escooter.
        username - The user that asked for the routes.
        maxNumberOfSuggestions - The maximum number of suggestions to provide.
        ascendingOrder - If routes should be ordered by ascending or descending order
        sortingCriteria - The criteria to use for ordering "energy", "shortest_distance", "number_of_points".
        inputPOIs - Path to file that contains the POIs that the route must go through, according to file input/pois.csv. By default, the file is empty.
        outputFileName - Write to the file the Route between two parks according to file output/paths.csv. More than one path may exist.
        Returns:
        The number of suggestions

      • getInvoiceForMonth

        double getInvoiceForMonth(int month,
                          String username,
                          String outputPath)
        Get the current invoice for the current month, for a specific user. This should include all loans that were charged the user, the number of points the user had before the actual month, the number of points earned during the month, the number of points converted to euros.
        Parameters:
        month - The month of the invoice e.g. 1 for January.
        username - The user for which the invoice should be created.
        outputPath - Path to file where the invoice should be written, according to file output/invoice.csv.
        Returns:
        User debt in euros rounded to two decimal places.
